The paper discusses game-theoretic approaches to security, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper specifically focuses on security games, which can be classified under the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of randomized strategies and uncertainty, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes an extensive-form game model, which is a common topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
